      "content": "it just seems like you're framing the strict sentencing side as something people just \"argue\" for even though the data is mixed. if the long-term costs are so high, isn't it basically a proven fact that these laws are a failure? feels like you're treating the reform side as a scientific conclusion and the deterrence side as just an opinion.",
